<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>She started her business, Thabo Makhetha Designs, in 2009 after graduating from Nelson Mandela University.“We all know there are not enough jobs but that didn’t bother me because I was studying fashion design and had just started my own business.” Thabo was born in Lesotho but grew up in Joburg and various other cities. Her designs stand out because they are made from traditional Sotho blankets.“I don’t only design for Sotho people but for everyone who likes quality.” She makes scarves which she sells for R450, her short capes go for R1 000 to R1 600, long capes are R2 000 and full jackets are R6 000.“My business is growing each year and I’m happy people are supporting it,” said Thabo.“It’s important to believe in yourself and give your all to whatever you do,” she said.Thabo said to order any of her designs, people may contact her on 072 347 8849, email design@makhetha.co.za or visit www.thabomakhetha.com